s/evert/subscriptions","organizations_url":"https://api.github.com/users/evert/orgs","repos_url":"https://api.github.com/users/evert/repos","events_url":"https://api.github.com/users/evert/events{/privacy}","received_events_url":"https://api.github.com/users/evert/received_events","type":"user","site_admin":false},"created_at":"2013-07-14t13:24:10z","updated_at":"2013-07-14t13:24:10z","body":"the owner is not a user id, it must be a relative path (for example `principals/users/<username>`).\r\n\r\nif somebody does not have a certain permission, you don't `null` the principal, instead you should not return the privilege at all.\r\n\r\n`owncloudns?` is not a valid xml namespace. you must indeed also add this privilege to getsupportedprivilegeset().\r\n\r\n"},{"url":"https://api.github.com/repos/owncloud/core/issues/comments/20939894","html_url":"https://github.com/owncloud/core/issues/3602#issuecomment-20939894","issue_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/owncloud/core/issues/3602","id":20939894,"user":{"login":"mtgap","id":1097106,"avatar_url":"https://gravatar.com/avatar/454a73ee5feeb428d0c163a48903332c?d=https%3a%2f%2fidenticons.github.com%2f52d29a66f285a1d61125dd69ac0766b2.png&r=x","gravatar_id":"454a73ee5feeb428d0c163a48903332c","url":"https://api.github.com/users/mtgap","html_url":"https://github.com/mtgap","followers_url":"https://api.github.com/users/mtgap/followers","following_url":"https://api.github.com/users/mtgap/following{/other_user}","gists_url":"https://api.github.com/users/mtgap/gists{/gist_id}","starred_url":"https://api.github.com/users/mtgap/starred{/owner}{/repo}","subscriptions_url":"https://api.github.com/users/mtgap/subscriptions","organizations_url":"https://api.github.com/users/mtgap/orgs","repos_url":"https://api.github.com/users/mtgap/repos","events_url":"https://api.github.com/users/mtgap/events{/privacy}","received_events_url":"https://api.github.com/users/mtgap/received_events","type":"user","site_admin":false},"created_at":"2013-07-14t17:23:01z","updated_at":"2013-07-14t17:23:01z","body":"thanks. is it necessary to return the owner in our case because we already restrict the logged in user to their own files in owncloud's filesystem?\r\n\r\nthat namespace was just a placeholder. i'm supposed to add the namespace to the public property $xmlnamespaces correct? something like 'http://owncloud.org/ns' => 'oc' in the array?"},{"url":"https://api.github.com/repos/owncloud/core/issues/comments/20947918","html_url":"https://github.com/owncloud/core/issues/3602#issuecomment-20947918","issue_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/owncloud/core/issues/3602","id":20947918,"user":{"login":"evert","id":178960,"avatar_url":"https://gravatar.com/avatar/7d76e2bb6f8c962a5628093c9f5bc6fb?d=https%3a%2f%2fidenticons.github.com%2f46192a8c94cd97601476c800f3d5f483.png&r=x","gravatar_id":"7d76e2bb6f8c962a5628093c9f5bc6fb","url":"https://api.github.com/users/evert","html_url":"https://github.com/evert","followers_url":"https://api.github.com/users/evert/followers","following_url":"https://api.github.com/users/evert/following{/other_user}","gists_url":"https://api.github.com/users/evert/gists{/gist_id}","starred_url":"https://api.github.com/users/evert/starred{/owner}{/repo}","subscriptions_url":"https://api.github.com/users/evert/subscriptions","organizations_url":"https://api.github.com/users/evert/orgs","repos_url":"https://api.github.com/users/evert/repos","events_url":"https://api.github.com/users/evert/events{/privacy}","received_events_url":"https://api.github.com/users/evert/received_events","type":"user","site_admin":false},"created_at":"2013-07-15t00:57:15z","updated_at":"2013-07-15t00:57:15z","body":"the contents of the current-user-privilege-set property is determined based on the privilege information, which principal is logged in, which principal(-groups) that principal belongs to and a few more factors.\r\n\r\nyou could replace a principal url by the string `{dav:}authenticated', implying that any authenticated user has that privilege. if you dynamically set those privileges based on the currently logged in user, i guess you would mostly achieve the same result.\r\n\r\nif you can easily get access to the correct principal url, i'd recommend doing that though. "},{"url":"https://api.github.com/repos/owncloud/core/issues/comments/21154184","html_url":"https://github.com/owncloud/core/issues/3602#issuecomment-21154184","issue_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/owncloud/core/issues/3602","id":21154184,"user":{"login":"mtgap","id":1097106,"avatar_url":"https://gravatar.com/avatar/454a73ee5feeb428d0c163a48903332c?d=https%3a%2f%2fidenticons.github.com%2f52d29a66f285a1d61125dd69ac0766b2.png&r=x","gravatar_id":"454a73ee5feeb428d0c163a48903332c","url":"https://api.github.com/users/mtgap","html_url":"https://github.com/mtgap","followers_url":"https://api.github.com/users/mtgap/followers","following_url":"https://api.github.com/users/mtgap/following{/other_user}","gists_url":"https://api.github.com/users/mtgap/gists{/gist_id}","starred_url":"https://api.github.com/users/mtgap/starred{/owner}{/repo}","subscriptions_url":"https://api.github.com/users/mtgap/subscriptions","organizations_url":"https://api.github.com/users/mtgap/orgs","repos_url":"https://api.github.com/users/mtgap/repos","events_url":"https://api.github.com/users/mtgap/events{/privacy}","received_events_url":"https://api.github.com/users/mtgap/received_events","type":"user","site_admin":false},"created_at":"2013-07-17t23:56:57z","updated_at":"2013-07-17t23:56:57z","body":"@evert could you give this a look: https://gist.github.com/mtgap/0945a78e633ae72679cc#file-gistfile1-php-l163\r\nhttps://gist.github.com/mtgap/0945a78e633ae72679cc#file-gistfile1-php-l179\r\n\r\nan update for everyone else, after talking to @evert i decided to avoid the acl plugin because our own internal filesystem already handles most of the work that the plugin does. the permissions are still being returned as dav properties, except for the custom share property. the unique id is also included in the properties, as requested here: #3593 "},{"url":"https://api.github.com/repos/owncloud/core/issues/comments/21155222","html_url":"https://github.com/owncloud/core/issues/3602#issuecomment-21155222","issue_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/owncloud/core/issues/3602","id":21155222,"user":{"login":"evert","id":178960,"avatar_url":"https://gravatar.com/avatar/7d76e2bb6f8c962a5628093c9f5bc6fb?d=https%3a%2f%2fidenticons.github.com%2f46192a8c94cd97601476c800f3d5f483.png&r=x","gravatar_id":"7d76e2bb6f8c962a5628093c9f5bc6fb","url":"https://api.github.com/users/evert","html_url":"https://github.com/evert","followers_url":"https://api.github.com/users/evert/followers","following_url":"https://api.github.com/users/evert/following{/other_user}","gists_url":"https://api.github.com/users/evert/gists{/gist_id}","starred_url":"https://api.github.com/users/evert/starred{/owner}{/repo}","subscriptions_url":"https://api.github.com/users/evert/subscriptions","organizations_url":"https://api.github.com/users/evert/orgs","repos_url":"https://api.github.com/users/evert/repos","events_url":"https://api.github.com/users/evert/events{/privacy}","received_events_url":"https://api.github.com/users/evert/received_events","type":"user","site_admin":false},"created_at":"2013-07-18t00:24:58z","updated_at":"2013-07-18t00:24:58z","body":"looks fine to me on the surface =)\r\n\r\nyou're not rfc3744 complaint of course, but you're re-using the properties which is a step in the right direction :)\r\n\r\nmy humble guess is that as your requirements expand and change over the years you'll slowly adopt more rfc3744 features though :p"}]